==著名葬礼==
一些国家级和其他场面宏大葬礼曾经在此举行。这些葬礼通常有漫长的送葬队伍，由白宫或者国会山开始，沿着宾夕法尼亚大道至E街SE，后转向墓地。一部分路面由国会特别拨款为送葬设计。这些规格和制式是以后[[State_funerals_in_the_United_States|美国国葬]]的基础形制，比方说林肯总统和约翰肯尼迪总统的国葬。<ref>Johnson and Johnson, Chapter 2, "The Grand Procession to the National Burial Ground."</ref>

这些葬礼包括：
*美国副总统[[乔治·克林顿|乔治·克林顿]]，1812年4月22日。送葬队伍包括美国总统[[詹姆斯·麦迪逊|詹姆斯·麦迪逊]]和两院议员。<ref>[http://www.congressionalcemetery.org/vice-president-george-clinton Vice President George Clinton] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110817052556/http://www.congressionalcemetery.org/vice-president-george-clinton |date=2011-08-17 }}, reprinted from The [[National_Intelligencer|National Intelligencer]] by the Association for the Preservation of Historic Congressional Cemetery, accessed April 27, 2012.</ref>
*美国第9任总统[[威廉·亨利·哈里森|威廉·亨利·哈里森]]，1841年。After services at the [[White_House|White House]] the procession included the new President [[John_Tyler|John Tyler]] and former President John Quincy Adams, as well as officers and members of the Congress and the state legislature of Maryland, extending over two miles long.<ref>[http://www.congressionalcemetery.org/president-william-henry-harrison President William Henry Harrison] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141012172257/http://www.congressionalcemetery.org/president-william-henry-harrison |date=2014-10-12 }}, reprinted from The [[National_Intelligencer|National Intelligencer]] by the Association for the Preservation of Historic Congressional Cemetery, accessed April 27, 2012.</ref>
*埃布尔·帕克·厄普舍（Abel Paker Upshur），美国律师、政治家，曾任美国海军部长和美国国务卿，[[Thomas_W._Gilmer|Thomas W. Gilmer]], Secretary of the Navy, Commodore [[Beverly_Kennon|Beverly Kennon]], Chief of the Bureau of Construction & Equipment, [[David_Gardiner_(John_Tyler_family)|David Gardiner]], former Senator from New York, victims of a February 28, 1844 explosion on the [[USS_Princeton_(1843)|USS ''Princeton'']]. [[Virgil_Maxcy|Virgil Maxcy]], Chargé d'Affaires of the United States to Belgium was also killed in the explosion, but was buried separately in his family plot.<ref>[http://www.congressionalcemetery.org/secretary-abel-p-upshur-secretary-thomas-wgilmer-commodore-beverly-kennon-hon-david-gardiner-hon-vir Victims of the USS Princeton explosion] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009095803/http://www.congressionalcemetery.org/secretary-abel-p-upshur-secretary-thomas-wgilmer-commodore-beverly-kennon-hon-david-gardiner-hon-vir |date=2013-10-09 }}, reprinted from February 29, 1844 edition of The [[National_Intelligencer|National Intelligencer]] by the Association for the Preservation of Historic Congressional Cemetery, accessed April 27, 2012.</ref>
*美国第六任总统[[约翰·昆西·亚当斯|约翰·昆西·亚当斯]]，1848年2月28日下葬。<ref>[http://www.congressionalcemetery.org/president-john-quincy-adams President John Quincy Adams] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009093956/http://www.congressionalcemetery.org/president-john-quincy-adams |date=2013-10-09 }} includes reprints from 1848 editions of the National Intelligencer,  Association for the Preservation of Historic Congressional Cemetery, accessed May 2, 2012.</ref>
*多莉·麦迪逊，前第一夫人，1849年7月16日下葬。President Zachary Taylor and his Cabinet attended services at [[St._John's_Episcopal_Church,_Lafayette_Square_(Washington,_D.C.)|St. John's Church]] in [[Lafayette_Square_Historic_District_(Washington,_D.C.)|Lafayette Square]], whence the cortege proceeded to the Public Vault at the Congressional Cemetery.<ref>[http://www.congressionalcemetery.org/first-lady-dolley-p-madison First Lady Dolley P. Madison] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009095657/http://www.congressionalcemetery.org/first-lady-dolley-p-madison |date=2013-10-09 }} includes reprints from 1849 editions of the National Intelligencer,  Association for the Preservation of Historic Congressional Cemetery, accessed May 2, 2012.</ref>
*美国第12任美国总统[[扎卡里·泰勒|扎卡里·泰勒]]，1850年7月13日下葬。Proceeding from the [[White_House|White House]], the cortege included the new President [[Millard_Fillmore|Millard Fillmore]], the Cabinet, the officers and members of both houses of Congress, numerous military units, and Taylor's favorite horse, Old Whitey.<ref>[http://www.congressionalcemetery.org/president-zachary-taylor President Zachary Taylor] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131011091659/http://www.congressionalcemetery.org/president-zachary-taylor |date=2013-10-11 }} includes reprints from 1850 editions of the National Intelligencer,  Association for the Preservation of Historic Congressional Cemetery, accessed May 2, 2012.</ref>

